e it, and, especially, the consequences of modernization for the political freedom of citizens to influence the course of their society via democratic politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aPolitics and culture. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aSmyth Van Weesep, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030011081440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013482740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300134827423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300134827/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY